BINARY_OPERATOR_EXPRESSION

public static final Expression.ExpressionType BINARY_OPERATOR_EXPRESSION
Constant for all expressions with one operator and two operands.

Examples for such expressions are assignment expressions, shift expressions, comparison expressions and so on. I.e. all expressions with one operator and an operand on the left and right side of that operator must be marked by this constant.
